            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#martaf #AA">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w>Ἐτελεύτησεν</w>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name>Τύχημος</name></persName> <w>τῇ</w>
                    <lb n="3"/><w><expan><abbr>πρ</abbr><ex>ὸ</ex></expan></w> <num value="15">δεκαπέντε</num> <w>κα<lb n="4" break="no"/>λανδῶν</w> <w>Ἰενουαρί<lb n="5" break="no"/>ων</w> <w>ζήσας</w> <w>ἒτη</w> <num value="60">π</num>
                    <lb n="6"/><w>καλὸν</w> <w>βίον</w> <w>ζήσας</w>
                    <lb n="7"/><w>ἠγόρασεν</w> <w>ἑαυτῷ</w> <w>καὶ</w>
                    <lb n="8"/><w>τοῖς</w> <w>ἠδίοις</w> <g ref="#christogram">☧</g>
                    <lb n="9"/> <g ref="#cross">+</g>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#martaf">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based on photograph</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 2"><note>lapis: Τύχημος (i.e. Τύχιμος); Ferrua: Εὐτυχήμος (i.e. Εὐθυδήμος); Amico: Τύχηλλος</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 4"><note>Kirchhoff: Ἰ[α]νυαρίων; Kaibel, Wessel, Korhonen: Ἰενυαρίων</note></app>
                    <app loc="lines 8-9"><note>Wessel and Korhonen read two Christograms</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#martaf #AA">
                <p>Tychemos died 15 days before the Kalends of January, having lived 80 years. Having lived a good life, he purchased this (tomb) for him and his relatives.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#martaf">
                <p>Tychemos è morto 15 giorni prima delle Calende di gennaio, avendo vissuto 80 anni. Avendo vissuto una bella vita, acquistò questo (sepolcro) per lui e i suoi.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#martaf">
                <p>This Christian epitaph does not present the <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐνθάδε κεῖται</foreign> formula, but directly the date of death expressed by the aorist of <foreign xml:lang="grc">τελευτάω</foreign> and the age of the deceased with the participle <foreign xml:lang="grc">ζήσας</foreign>. This is followed by the indication of the purchase of the tomb (with the aorist of <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀγοράζω</foreign>) by the deceased, for him and his descendants (<foreign xml:lang="grc">ἠδίοις</foreign> is an hypercorrection): for the reference to the descendants in pagan and Christian epitaphs in Catania, see IG 14.563 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001382">ISic001382</ref>, SEG XVII 440 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001628">ISic001628</ref>. On <foreign xml:lang="grc">καλὸν βίον ζήσας</foreign>/<foreign xml:lang="grc">βιώσας</foreign>, see also IGUR 2.626. The name of the deceased, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Τύχημος</foreign> (probably <foreign xml:lang="grc">Τύχιμος</foreign>), is not otherwise attested; Ferrua’s reading is palaeographically improbable (furthermore, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Εὐτύχημος</foreign> is not attested in imperial age, see BCH 45 (1921) p. 19 III, 101 from Kythera, 3rd cent. BCE), as well as Leclercq’s reading <foreign xml:lang="grc">Τύχηλλος</foreign>.</p>
		    <p>Note that the text has been badly overpainted in early modern times, leading to several misleading letter forms (e.g. initial epsilon as sigma)</p>
            </div>
